replies.body:
Yes, that is why they forcibly teleported Kassadin back to the institute when he attacked Malzahar, who was trying to stop him from continuing his void bringing past times, during one of the Journal of Justice's(I think that is where I saw the comic)

And for some more concrete evidence;

And what about the Kayle/Morgana storyline? They want to kill each other, but until their servitude is over they content themselves with destroying each other inside the rift. If they were allowed to attack each other where the deaths would be permanent, why would they bother with the rift for a second? Especially Kayle, who fears the power that Morgana was given and believes that it could destroy her world's order if it was mastered. Wouldn't she want to kill Morgana **before** she has 1000 years to practice it? (which is how long Kayle's servitude is for) If they had no such constraints, then many "I want to find and kill you" storylines would be resolved quickly. Like the Renekton and Nasus one.
